            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-11-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-11-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="442" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                <head>No. 1.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Marquis of
                                            Salisbury</gloss> to Mr. <persName type="to">Herbert</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegraphic]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-11-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 5, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You may, if the United States Government have not yet been
                                    informed, write to Secretary of State that, by instructions from
                                    Her Majesty’s Government, you have, in the absence of Lord
                                    Sackville, been placed in charge of the legation.</p>
            </div>
